ntribution to the literature on the Middle East, as well as a new perspective on women and on gender issues in the context of developing modernity in the region.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aLebanesexHistoryxUnited States. 0aLebanesezUnited StatesxHistory. 0aMiddle classxHistoryxLebanon. 0aMiddle classzLebanonxHistory. 0aReturn migrationxHistoryxLebanon. 0aReturn migrationzLebanonxHistory. 0aSex rolexHistoryxLebanon. 0aSex rolezLebanonxHistory. 4aGeneral. 4aHistory. 4aMiddle East. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh1 aKhater, Akram Fouad, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt0 cprintz978052022740840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093568640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520935686423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520935686/original  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles